webResources.textAttributionSnippet: (en) In 1745 the work began to expand the medieval church building of the parish in Vist. The new church received a very lavish interior. The costs could be shared by no fewer one three sellers in the parish who, in return, had the patronate court alternated among themselves. The inconspicuous roof of the church was painted by Sven Gustavsson Stoltz of Vadstena. The altarpiece, made by Johan Jerling, was shot by Countess Christina Piper at Sturefors. For the holders of the same estate, the relative was completed closest to the right - https://www.europeana.eu/item/73/S_OM_photo_OMFB000567. AB Flygtrafik. Östergötlands museum - http://digitaltmuseum.se/021016419882. Public Domain Mark - http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/
